- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper involves the use of a Hierarchical Inverse Dynamics (HID) for applying the generated trajectories to the full robot, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a swing foot trajectory modification strategy using DCM measurement, which involves the use of AI techniques. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although not explicitly mentioned, the use of machine learning techniques cannot be ruled out in the proposed method. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although not directly related, the use of computer vision techniques for biped robot navigation and obstacle avoidance cannot be ruled out.
